<subSubSection id="B8AC2C8CDC51FF85FF41FD7CAA70FC2D" pageId="3" pageNumber="524" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F0097F07DC51FF85FF41FD7CAA70FC2D" blockId="3.[151,1437,666,979]" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis id="C2C2A315DC51FF85FF41FD7CAE55FD15" bold="true" box="[151,273,666,691]" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new genus 
<taxonomicName id="37B60484DC51FF85FE10FD7CAD2AFD15" authority="Yamaguchi &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis, 2017" authorityName="Yamaguchi &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis" authorityYear="2017" box="[454,622,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hirsutophallus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="C2C2A315DC51FF85FE10FD7CAD2AFD15" box="[454,622,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">Hirsutophallus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="37B60484DC51FF85FC0BFD7CABC9FD15" box="[989,1165,666,691]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Poecilognathini">Poecilognathini</taxonomicName>
by the presence of large and short lower lobes on the epiphallus, very different from the long and slender lower lobes of other genera, presence of striking large and curved lateral lobes on the epiphallus, with long dorsal macrosetae, not found in any other genus, and presence of long dorsal macrosetae on the penial guide of the distiphallus, which is absent in the other genera. The gonocoxite with a medial process that is large basally and acute on apex in lateral view, with apical and ventral short spines together with the presence of ventral spines on posterior process and furca V-shaped with very long and curved apical arms, easily segregates 
<taxonomicName id="37B60484DC51FF85FCC0FC94ACFAFC2D" authority="Yamaguchi &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis, 2017" authorityName="Yamaguchi &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis" authorityYear="2017" box="[790,958,882,907]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hirsutophallus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="533" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="C2C2A315DC51FF85FCC0FC94ACFAFC2D" box="[790,958,882,907]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">Hirsutophallus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all members of 
<taxonomicName id="37B60484DC51FF85FB67FC94AA74FC2D" authorityName="Yamaguchi &amp; Lamas &amp; Evenhuis" authorityYear="2017" box="[1201,1328,882,907]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Phthiriinae">Phthiriinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B8AC2C8CDC51FF85FF11FC70AD77FC74" pageId="3" pageNumber="524" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F0097F07DC51FF85FF11FC70AD77FC74" blockId="3.[151,1437,666,979]" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">
<emphasis id="C2C2A315DC51FF85FF11FC70AE0AFC09" bold="true" box="[199,334,918,943]" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic epithet derives from Latin 
<emphasis id="C2C2A315DC51FF85FCDEFC70AC26FC09" box="[776,866,918,943]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">hirsutus</emphasis>
, meaning hairy or bristly, and 
<emphasis id="C2C2A315DC51FF85FB61FC70AA4DFC09" box="[1207,1289,918,943]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="524">phallus</emphasis>
, in reference to the male reproductive component.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
